rComments: Professor Atance is a great prof. She is caring, has clear grading criteria and her lectures are interesting. Would recommend!
She is amazing. So kind and helpful. 10/10 would reccomend. Would take her again!!

Very interesting lectures. Does not always go through everything in class so the textbook is a must. It is important to read the readings she assigns to fully understand all the concepts. Gives a lot of examples. Tests and quizzes are fairly simple. If you are really interested in child psychology, this is an amazing class.
She actually cares about her students, shes very passionate about psych and I looked forward to her lectures! If you do the readings and take notes from the lectures you'll do great!

Lectures were good and engaging. However, exams were designed to trick students and also tested on obscure material from the textbook. The weighting distribution of assignments was very strange and these assignments were also marked with surprising difficulty

Really nice prof, very approachable. Exams are a little unfair for the amount of work you put in. Pay attention to little details she mentions in class. Textbook is good for overall topics but unnecessary to read it all. Concept checks in text  questions on tests.

Prof Atance is nice and her classes are really interesting. Although her midterm was hard. You really have to read the textbook and consider all the details when you are studying. Overall, she is a good prof, but be prepared to read.

Prof. Atance is a good prof in some ways. My personal problem was that she focused mostly on methods of experiments and for the midterm and final you had to memorize these methods, which I found inapplicable to real life and unhelpful to my learning and future career. She was a good lecturer, however, and very caring and funny.

The professor is nice, but she only teaches about studies done on cognitive development and for the midterm you need to memorize what the purpose and results were for each study. There is a group research project and everyone has to write their own research paper. This class is very dry, so take it if you really want to learn about children

Very nice professor, cares about her students and takes the time to get to know you personally. Make sure you go to class. It really helps. Lab work is very easy, midterms are extremely fair and not hard if you study. i absolutely loved her class.

Good Professor. Covered a lot of material in class that is not in text - so make sure that you attend class! Exams are fair - study both from the text and class notes! All in all it was a good class and I would definitely reccommend taking it!

Her exams were comprehensive but the material is not hard to understand or remember. Exams were fair and the short questions were pretty obvious, as she basically rehearses them in class. Go to class - the material is clear and she is organized (nice too!). We had an assignment and several one-page opinion papers. Not too much work and easy marks.
I thought the short answer questions were pretty obvious, you could tell what was coming. This class was really clear, everything was presented really well.

Really enjoyed this class!! She's a great teacher, who is really passionate about what she teaches.  The slides are well prepared and easy to study from.  the midterms were pretty hard.  The short answers tested on such little nit picky things in the lectures!  But just study everything and anything and you'll do fine!!
Her is a very good lecturer and presents the material with enthusiasm.  She is a brilliant woman and she is not bad looking.
her lectures are really interesting and very clear HOWEVER she spends a lot of time on a few examples and tests on small details of theories. The short answer questions on her tests are HARD
Nice prof.Intelligent.Covered material well. Provides class slides online.
great teacher  and very hot
Make sure to attend the lectures and for the written assignment pay attention to grammar and spelling!  Professor is a dynamic young woman and she is teaching her course well.
not bad class, intelligent prof, seemed nice.
Decent prof, but lectures seemed like she was reading straight from her overheads, which doesn't make for an interesting class.
No Comments
knows her stuff
